  <title>What does kinematically-defined mean?</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Definition<keyword>kinematically-defined</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">What does kinematically-defined mean?</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Kinematic states of <text styleclass="Element-Header">Parts</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_"><text styleclass="Body Text">There are two kinematic-states of </text><text styleclass="Element-Header">Parts</text><text styleclass="Body Text">.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="3" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:205px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2" style="text-align:right;"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Not kinematically-defined</text> : </para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The state of a <text styleclass="Element">Part</text> when it has <text styleclass="VariableName-small" style="color:#ff0000;">one</text> or <text styleclass="VariableName-small" style="color:#ff0000;">more</text> degrees-of-freedom.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:205px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2" style="text-align:right;"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">kinematically-defined</text> : </para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The state of a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text> when it has <text styleclass="VariableName-small" style="color:#ff0000;">zero</text>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">Mobility</text>. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">Its position, velocity, and acceleration are fully specified. </para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Mobility of a Kinematic-chain = </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> # Degrees-of-Freedom – # Motion-Dimensions.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName"># Degrees-of-Freedom <equation style="vertical-align:baseline;vertical-align:middle"><![CDATA[= 3.\left( N-1 \right)-2.J]]></equation></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">N = Number of <text styleclass="Element">Parts</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">J= Number of <text styleclass="Element">Joints</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">All <text styleclass="Element-Header">Parts</text> in the model must be <text styleclass="VariableName">kinematically-defined</text>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">before</text> you should analyse any motion and force data.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
